        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Dyke believes the chip shortage will improve “in the coming months” that doesn’t mean production levels will be back to normal then. In fact, Goldman Sachs paints a fairly bleak picture, predicting new car inventories will stay below what they were before the pandemic and shutdowns throughout 2022. In other words, we might not be completely out of the woods for over a year, if even then.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
